## Resolved mutable: mut-1783243147665

exec_js-1.json: minimal execSync('node -e console.log(1)') inside wasm exec_js host returned ok:true exit_code:0 duration_ms:229, watcher .status.json ts advanced normally (no restart) -- so bare child_process.execSync is NOT fatal to the wasm host. Crash is specific to the 3 poisoned tasks' actual payload (bun x ccsniff@latest --Ndiscipline --since 45m with timeout:120000, gh run list --repo with timeout:30000x6, npm view with timeout:30000x3) -- likely a long-lived/hanging child process (bun x resolving deps over network, or gh/npm needing auth/network the sandboxed wasm host lacks) that outlives the wasm task's own execution budget and takes the host down with it, rather than execSync itself being unsupported. Workaround applied: moved poisoned tasks to .gm/exec-spool/.poisoned-tasks/, watcher stable since. Root-cause-to-single-line: host needs a hard subprocess wall-clock/resource ceiling independent of the JS-side timeout param so a hung child can't kill the watcher process -- upstream rs-plugkit/rs-exec fix, out of gm-repo scope, not fixed here.